OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F413A1780927877
OL,3,CReading warehouse fined thousands for
OL,4,Crat infestation and food hygiene
OL,5,Cbreaches
OL,7,FUntraceable meat, food contaminated by
OL,8,Frat urine and fish rotting near the
OL,9,Ftoilet are just some of the reasons
OL,10,Fwhy a food operator at a warehouse in
OL,11,FReading has been fined thousands.
OL,13,FSerious health risks were identified
OL,14,Fat Kingdom Family Ltd, a food
OL,15,Fwarehouse storing frozen and dry goods
OL,16,Ffor retail shops in Reading, by the
OL,17,Fcouncil's food and safety team.
OL,19,FOn 18th May the company's sole
OL,20,Fdirector, Mr Ameyaw, pleaded guilty to
OL,21,Ffive food hygiene offences including:
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G1/9
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,414,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41302
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F413A1780927877
OL,3,CReading warehouse fined thousands for
OL,4,Crat infestation and food hygiene
OL,5,Cbreaches
OL,7,FHe was fined #2,300, ordered to pay
OL,8,Fthe victim a surcharge of #920 and
OL,9,Fcontribute towards the councils legal
OL,10,Fcosts of #1,000.
OL,12,FThe charges come three years after
OL,13,Fconcerns were first raised about the
OL,14,Ffood warehouse.
OL,16,FIn 2024, officers seized an estimated
OL,17,F400kg of illegal meat products in
OL,18,Funlabelled black bin bags stored in a
OL,19,Fwalk-in freezer.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G2/9
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,414,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41303
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F413A1780927877
OL,3,CReading warehouse fined thousands for
OL,4,Crat infestation and food hygiene
OL,5,Cbreaches
OL,7,FA number of food businesses were found
OL,8,Fto be operating in the warehouse
OL,9,Fwithout registration with the Food and
OL,10,FSafety team.
OL,12,FReading Magistrates' Court approved
OL,13,Fthe condemnation of the unsafe food,
OL,14,Fand Kingdom Family Ltd was ordered to
OL,15,Fpay over #6,000 in costs to the
OL,16,Fcouncil.
OL,18,FIn October 2024, Council Food Safety
OL,19,FOfficers discovered more untraceable
OL,20,Fmeat and a widespread rat infestation.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G3/9
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,414,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41304
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F413A1780927877
OL,3,CReading warehouse fined thousands for
OL,4,Crat infestation and food hygiene
OL,5,Cbreaches
OL,7,FLarge quantities of food was gnawed
OL,8,Fand contaminated with rat urine and
OL,9,Ffaeces, including sacks of rice, corn
OL,10,Fdough, cassava flour and tinned goods.
OL,12,FDespite formal warnings, the food
OL,13,Fbusiness operator failed to take
OL,14,Faction to address the infestation and
OL,15,Fdispose of contaminated stock.
OL,17,FOfficers were denied access for follow-
OL,18,Fup inspections, prompting Reading
OL,19,FCouncil to obtain a warrant in
OL,20,FNovember to re-enter the premises.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G4/9
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
